# About aptitude
# aptitude is a front-end to dpkg, the Debian package management tool. 
# It displays a list of software packages and allows the user to interactively pick packages to install or remove. 
# It has an especially powerful search system utilizing flexible search patterns. 
# It was initially created for Debian, but has appeared in RPM Package Manager (RPM) based distributions as well (such as Conectiva).
#
# Reference:
# https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aptitude_(software)


# To search for packages:
aptitude search "whatever"

# To display package records for the named package(s):
aptitude show pkg(s)

# To install a package:
aptitude install package

# To remove a package:
aptitude remove package

# To remove unnecessary package:
aptitude autoclean

